<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 16 at 2:23AM CST  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Red
River County through 300 AM CST...
At 223 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pattonville, or 13 miles southeast of Paris, moving northeast at 55
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Clarksville, Bogata, Bagwell, Manchester, Detroit, Deport and Negley.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
